An style 'container' is created by called 
  styled.[html element type]`
	
  // css here

`

e.g. const StyledForum = styled.div`
  color: blue;
`

- Normal css can be created in this template string 
- It will pass to any nested components.

-------------

In a react component e.g:

<StyledForum>
	<Forum>
</StyledForum>

easy peasy.

----------------
Global Styles:
	The App top level is wrapped in a 'Fragment' container, 
	and <GlobalStyles> is a sibling. This applies global styles to the whole app.
	Let's add any @import stuff to App.css
	
		

